de.adorsys.opba.protocol.api.ais

Interface ListAccounts

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Action<ListAccountsRequest,AccountListBody>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HbciListAccountsEntrypoint, Xs2aListAccountsEntrypoint
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ListAccounts
extends Action<ListAccountsRequest,AccountListBody>
    Called to get PSU account list from ASPSP using AIS (Account Information Service). Typical outcomes:
    • SuccessResult

      Returned when request was successful. Contains requested account list.

    • ValidationErrorResult

      Returned when PSU input is required (or consent was missing). Causes redirection to Consent authorization.

    • AuthorizationRequiredResult

      Returned when no matching consent was found for the request and PSU needs to authorize new consent. Causes redirection to Consent authorization.

      • Methods inherited from interface de.adorsys.opba.protocol.api.Action
